		<section>
			<section.front>
				<doc.title toc-guid="I0d4b947bc08511d88885080020ab8e66">
					<head parent="doc.title">
						<label.name>&#167; </label.name>
						<label.designator>1:4.</label.designator>
						<headtext>Optional provisions of contract</headtext>
					</head>
				</doc.title>
			</section.front>
			<section.body>
				<para>
					<paratext>For tax purposes<footnote.reference refid="I01a2f010680911e88f4a9c1f64100601">1</footnote.reference>, real property is placed in one of four categories.</paratext>
				</para>
				<para>
					<paratext>The first category<footnote.reference refid="I01a2f010680911e88f4a9c1f64100602">7</footnote.reference> includes property held by a taxpayer for sale to customers. An occasional or casual sale is not covered, but once a taxpayer enters the business of selling real estate, he or she may become a dealer.</paratext>
				</para>
			</section.body>
			<page no="23"/>
		</section>
